com.mariangolea.fintracker.banks.csvparser.api.transaction

Class BankTransactionAbstractGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mariangolea.fintracker.banks.csvparser.api.transaction.BankTransactionAbstractGroup
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BankTransactionCompanyGroup, BankTransactionDefaultGroup

    public abstract class BankTransactionAbstractGroup
extends Object
    Base abstract class allowing grouping of transaction on criteria that inheritors need to support themselves.

    The application allows multiple levels of grouping:
    1. At the lowest level transactions are grouped based only on a single file for a single bank.
    1.1 if company is not identified, transactions from the same bank are grouped by transaction types (POS operations, credit, and so on) BankTransactionDefaultGroup.
    1.2. if company is identified, all transactions for a specific bank made for this company are grouped together BankTransactionCompanyGroup.
    2. If user has provided CSV reports from multiple banks, groups of the same type are merged together on the same principle BankTransactionUtils.processTransactions(java.util.List<com.mariangolea.fintracker.banks.csvparser.api.transaction.BankTransactionDefaultGroup>)
    3. User then has the option to define his own "categories" like "Food","Utilities", and so on. This latter one does not inherit from this class, but it makes sense to mention it in here.
    4. User can also create larger groups out of the ones from point 3.

    Author:
    mariangolea@gmail.com
